added.title: Operation Dude Rescue Part 1
added.description: When the male Titans are captured, it's up to Starfire and Raven to rescue them but they're going to need some extra girl power.

added.title: Operation Dude Rescue Part 2
added.description: Female heroes and villains unite to save Robin, Cyborg and Beast Boy from The Brain.

added.title: Open Door Policy
added.description: Still shipwrecked on a desert island, the Titans try to find food but stumble upon dinosaurs instead.

added.title: Summer Wish
added.description: When Craig decides to keep a lightning bug in a jar, he disrupts the delicate balance of Summer.

added.title: Turning the Tables
added.description: Craig dines at the restaurant where his older brother works and orders up a plate of REVENGE... and lots of breadsticks.

added.title: Kelsey the Author
added.description: Craig and Stacks help Kelsey become a real author turning her story into a book!

added.title: The Puppy
added.description: The kids finally get the puppy they always wanted, except . . . it's actually a turtle, and it hates them. After begging Dad for a puppy, the kids are taken aback when he comes home with a turtle. Despite the fact that the turtle turns out to be extremely aggressive (especially toward Gumball) they try their best to give it the love it deserves. This achieves nothing. The Evil Turtle escapes and goes on a rampage, and they have to find it before it destroys Elmore.

added.title: The Question
added.description: Gumball and Darwin seek the answer to the biggest question of all: what is the meaning of life? They need to understand the point of their lives, so resolve to seek advice from everyone in Elmore. They ask people, animals and even planets but their answer comes from an unexpected source.

added.title: The Skull
added.description: Gumball and Darwin make friends with classmate Clayton, a compulsive liar who can shape-change!

added.title: The Storm
added.description: Love is in the air and Gumball is caught in the center of an emotional hurricane - literally!

added.title: The Sweaters
added.description: Gumball and Darwin's reputation is challenged and they really couldn't care less...

added.title: Heatwave
added.description: Apple and Onion try to spread cheer during a city-wide heatwave.

added.title: Apple's in Charge
added.description: Apple is put in charge of the Dollar Store for the very first time.

added.title: Burger's Trampoline
added.description: Apple and Onion must find a way to use Burger's trampoline without making him feel used.

added.title: Baby Boi TP
added.description: Apple needs to acquire a lifetime supply of toilet paper to finish his modern art sculpture.

added.title: Not Funny
added.description: With their 6 month friend anniversary approaching, Apple has to find a way not to lose his best friend.

added.title: Boss For a Day
added.description: When Chata lets Vic be the boss of the taco stand for the day Vic decides to fire Val, which has disastrous consequences.

added.title: It Grows
added.description: As everyone celebrates Valentino for growing his first facial hair, a jealous Vic resorts to magical methods to grow a mustache and compete for attention.

added.title: Welcome to the Underworld 1
added.description: After Victor loses a wrestling match, Victor and Valentino journey to the underworld to seek advice from their uncle, a famous wrestler named El Toro.

added.title: Know It All
added.description: When Vic accidently unleashes evil bats from a cave, it's up to the boys and Don to protect the town, but Vic's know-it-all attitude keeps getting in the way.

added.title: Fistfull of Balloons
added.description: When Vic gets double-crossed during a water balloon fight, he goes on a revenge mission to find out who was responsible.

added.title: Rocknaldo
added.description: Ronaldo sets out to find all the rock people living in Beach City!

added.title: Lion 4: Alternate Ending
added.description: Lion coughs up a magical key, and Steven goes on a quest to find what it unlocks.

added.title: Steven vs. Amethyst
added.description: Steven and Amethyst get competitive while training with Pearl.

added.title: Beta
added.description: Steven and Amethyst visit some friends in the country but Amethyst isn't being herself.

added.title: Back to the Moon
added.description: Steven and the Gems revisit the Moon Base.

added.title: Tokyo Fun Part 1: Big Bugg Bash
added.description: While in Tokyo, Team Tennyson comes face to face with a horrible secret, Japan's hottest new restaurant is being run by the Bugg Brothers as a nefarious scheme to make loads of money off an unsuspecting public.

added.title: Tokyo Fun Part 2: Slamming It Up
added.description: While on a visit to the Sumo Slammers Amusement Park in Tokyo, Team Tennyson gets to watch a genuine sumo wrestling match as part of the Global Games, but when the mischievous Twain Twins crash the event to avenge their mother's medal snub years earlier, Ben must think things through if he is to stop the polarizing family!

added.title: Sweet Tooth
added.description: While on a trip to the dentist's office, a paranoid Ben grows uneasy over the dentist's odd behavior and goes into hiding, but when his suspicions prove right, and the dentist transforms into the monstrous Toothache, Ben must pull himself together if he is to save the day!

added.title: Medieval Upheaval
added.description: When Steam Smythe 'time travels' his way into a Renaissance Faire and kidnaps Max, Ben and Gwen must defeat him without breaking character.

added.title: Speed of Sound
added.description: Team Tennyson participates in the inaugural ride of the Sonitrain, the fastest train in the world, but when the conductor turns out to be Lord Decibel, Ben must derail his master plan if he is to save his family and the passengers on board the runaway train.

added.title: Xingo's World
added.description: Ben, Gwen, and Grandpa Max are on the road again and are supposed to be taking in the beautiful sights, but Ben refuses to put his video games away. Only the unexpected return of Xingo can spur him into action and teach him that the real world is just as important as any virtual one!

added.title: Roundabout Part 1
added.description: Forever Knight finally assembles his Round Table of young but super-powerful Knights, including— Ben?! With Ben's help, Forever Knight leads his new minions in an all-out attack on a Particle Accelerator - his true intention to transform it into a Time Machine and conquer history!

added.title: You Remind Me of Someone
added.description: Ben and Gwen look for the infamous Bojamboo (the Bigfoot of the South) and discover that it's actually the Forgeti, at the same time as Kevin 11, but when Ben and Kevin are blasted with the Forgeti's forgetfulness mist, they reverse roles and it's up to Gwen and Max to restore them back to normal.

added.title: Bottomless Ben
added.description: While visiting Carlsbad Caverns National Park, the Tennyson's come across the "Bottomless Pit", a naturally formed pit with no bottom. Ben fights his better judgment to jump in the pit and be the first person to find the bottom, until Kevin 11 shows up and starts to goad Ben into a contest to the bottom of the pit! The natural rivalry is put on hold, however, with the arrival of Breaker One-Nine, who has come to destroy the Caverns!

added.title: Digital Quality
added.description: Ben and Gwen don't want to go to the CD Library. CDs are for old people. Ew. Once Team Tennyson is there, Lord Decibel traps them inside and demands a ransom. Ben and Gwen find Kevin inside on a potentially nefarious quest of his own, but it turns out that Lord Decibel may have already found the item that they so desperately desire.

added.title: The Monsters in Your Head
added.description: Ben and Gwen learn a rumor of an alien invasion happening at the park they are camping at, but when they investigate, they discover a preserve containing a host of mutated creatures engineered by Animo! With the unexpected help of Kevin 11 and his family, Ben proves that the rumors are false, and that truth is stranger than fiction!

added.title: Popularity Conquest
added.description: When Mao Mao discovers that he is not as popular as Badgerclops and Adorabat, they decide to reinvent him as a kinder, cuddlier hero.

added.title: Thumb War
added.description: The gang decide to compete in the annual Thumb War competition, but a surprise forces Mao Mao to deal with the unthinkable... losing.

added.title: All By Mao Self
added.description: Mao Mao's desire to be a legend drives him to keep topping himself. But how much is enough?

added.title: He's the Sheriff
added.description: The gang struggles to get rid of the King when he joins them as their new deputy-for-a-day!

added.title: Bobo Chan
added.description: Badgerclops adopts an abandoned monster, but some things are better left in the wild.

added.title: Earth & Water
added.description: Princess Bubblegum subjects Flame Princess to a series of tests to gauge Flame Princess's fiery tendencies. When there's an emergency at the treehouse and Princess Bubblegum leaves Cinnamon Bun to watch Flame Princess, her experiment might literally backfire in her face.

added.title: Web Weirdos
added.description: When Finn gets trapped in a giant spider web, he ends up playing marriage counselor to a couple of grumpy arachnids.

added.title: Return to the Nightosphere
added.description: Marceline's dad banishes Finn and Jake to the Nightosphere, and it stinks. Literally.

added.title: You Made Me
added.description: When a creepy sleep-peeping Lemongrab upsets Princess Bubblegum with his creepy ways, Finn and Jake need to tend to some issues in the Outer Realm.

added.title: The Creeps
added.description: Finn and Jake receive an invitation to a masquerade dinner banquet from Count Creepystein.

added.title: Grown Up Stuff
added.description: Puppycorn doesn't want to grow up. To ease his woes, Unikitty spends the day teaching him all the fun things about being an adult.

added.title: Stop the Presses
added.description: Richard's newspapers aren't selling, so his friends pull out all the stops to put the printed word back on top.

added.title: Castles and Kitties
added.description: Score Creeper traps the gang in a fantasy role playing game where they must follow a complex set of rules to win their freedom.

added.title: Brain Trust
added.description: Dr. Fox accidentally transports the gang inside her brain, where they must control her movements to complete a dangerous experiment.

added.title: Old Lady Bodyguard
added.description: After being "bought" at a charity auction, Hawkodile is forced to spend the day as Old Lady Edith's personal bodyguard.

added.title: Too Cool
added.description: Puppycorn needs a lesson in how to be cool. The gang is more than happy to teach him, until his coolness unexpectedly freezes the whole kingdom.

added.title: Guardian of the Unikingdom
added.description: Hawkodile insists the Unikingdom is more dangerous than it looks and sets out to prove it by taking his friends on bodyguard patrol.

added.title: Cast Aside the Truth
added.description: Hawkodile breaks his arm in a careless spill and lies to his friends about the accident to keep from looking bad.

added.title: Unikitty and the Ice Pop Factory
added.description: An eccentric figure announces a contest to tour her marvelous ice pop factory, sending the gang on a frantic quest to find the winning popsicle stick.

added.title: Sunken Treasure
added.description: A relaxing beach day becomes an underwater adventure when Unikitty and her friends find a message in a bottle.

added.title: Never Trust a Human
added.description: A flashback episode tells the story of Young Wu and Young Garmadon meeting Aspheera and teaching her the secrets of Spinjitzu.

added.title: Under Siege
added.description: Having learned Master Wu is the "Treacherous One," the ninja find themselves under siege at the Monastery, trying to protect Wu from the wrath of Aspheera.

added.title: The Explorer's Club
added.description: The ninja must break into the Explorer's Club to obtain the second Scroll of Forbidden Spinjitzu, running afoul of the club's manager and irate club-members.

added.title: Vengeance Is Mine!
added.description: Aspheera arrives at the Monastery of Spinjitzu and confronts Wu, forcing one of the ninja to make a heroic sacrifice.

added.title: A Cold Goodbye
added.description: Having learned Zane is not dead, Master Wu prepares to go after him, but Lloyd and the other ninja take matters into their own hands and defy their Master.

added.title: Let's Meet Sonic
added.description: When world class hero SONIC THE HEDGEHOG visits the plaza, he teams up with KO to save the day.

added.title: Radical Rescue
added.description: Rad is forced to reconsider his identity when KO starts taking on some of his traits.

added.title: Carl
added.description: A pleasant weekend goes awry when a monster attacks.

added.title: Let's Fight to the End
added.description: When a fighting tournament is announced at the Plaza, there is more at stake than meets the eye.

added.title: Let's Watch the Boxmore Show
added.description: Our heroes discover that the Boxmore security camera feed is the most entertaining thing ever.

added.title: Date with Gus
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa and Pizza Steve accidentally ruin Mr. Gus' night, the two of them go undercover as Mr. Gus's date.

added.title: Gone to His Head
added.description: Uncle Grandpa's new found confidence makes his head big.

added.title: Do or Diaper
added.description: Mordecai has to kiss Margaret by the end of the week or else wear a diaper.

added.title: Country Club
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to rescue the golf cart from a bunch of rich people at a country club.

added.title: Lame Station
added.description: Pizza Steve tries desperately to make the others in the RV interested in his new game console.

added.title: Weekend at Benson's
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby accidentally knock out Benson and try to cover it up.

added.title: Yes Dude Yes
added.description: Mordecai wants to find a new girl to get over Margaret.

added.title: Los Monstruos de tu Cabeza
added.description: Ben y Gwen se enteran del rumor de una invasión alienígena en el parque en el que están acampando, pero cuando investigan, descubren una reserva que contiene una gran cantidad de criaturas mutantes diseñadas por Animo.

added.title: Me Recuerdas a Alguien
added.description: Ben y Gwen buscan al tristemente célebre Bojamboo (el Pie Grande del Sur) y descubren que en realidad se trata del Olvideti.

added.title: Rodeo Parte 1
added.description: El Caballero por Siempre finalmente reúne a su Mesa Redonda de Caballeros jóvenes pero superpoderosos... i¿incluido Ben?! Con la ayuda de Ben, el Caballero lidera a sus nuevos súbditos en un ataque generalizado contra un acelerador de partículas.

added.title: Big Tick
added.description: A giant alien tick that sucks planets dry, lands on Earth with the sole purpose of destroying the planet and only a new alien hero can stop it.

added.title: Splitsville
added.description: The girls learn to appreciate each others's style after having to each fight solo.

added.title: Gwen 10
added.description: Gwen gets her hands on the Omnitrix and all its powers and now Ben has to take a backseat as Gwen 10 battles Vilgax for control of the device.

added.title: Veamos el Show de Boxmore
added.description: Nuestros héroes descubren que las grabaciones de la cámara de seguridad de Boxmore son la cosa más divertida del mundo.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Super Sweet 6
added.description: Morbucks throws the biggest birthday party of all time, and Blossom is the only one not invited.

added.title: The Fan
added.description: Uncle Grandpa's number one fan gets more than he bargained for when Uncle Grandpa overstays his welcome.

added.title: Deseo de Verano
added.description: Cuando Craig decide dejar una luciérnaga dentro de un frasco, termina interfiriendo con el delicado equilibrio del verano.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Del Otro Lado de la Mesa
added.description: Craig almuerza en el restaurante donde trabaja su hermano mayor y pide un plato de VENGANZA… y muchos palitos de pan.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Kelsey la autora
added.description: iCraig y Stacks ayudan a Kelsey a convertirse en una verdadera autora al convertir su historia en un libro!
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Princess Buttercup
added.description: When Buttercup starts spending a lot of time with her new friends, a group of bad-girl skaters called The Derbytantes, it seems the Powerpuff Girls are down to two, which delights Princess Morbucks, who wants to fill the empty slot.

added.title: Tiger Trails
added.description: In the final moments of helping a kid, Uncle Grandpa just needs his trusty Giant Realistic Flying Tiger, but when he finds out she's gone, it sends UG on a journey to find the tiger and figure out why she left.

added.title: Just Set Up the Chairs
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby get distracted while setting up chairs for a kids birthday party and unleash a monster that terrorizes the entire park.

added.title: #LaDulceJusticia - Tercera parte
added.description: Cuando seis chicas comunes y corrientes descubren que cada una tiene un poder extraordinario diferente, deciden unir fuerzas para derrotar a algunos de los villanos más siniestros de Metrópolis en la parte 3 del episodio estreno.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: #SweetJustice Part 3
added.description: When six ordinary girls meet and discover that they each have extraordinary powers, they decide to join forces to take on one of Metropolis's most sinister villains.

added.title: #La dulce justicia - Cuarta parte
added.description: Cuando seis chicas comunes y corrientes descubren que cada una tiene un poder extraordinario diferente, deciden unir fuerzas para derrotar a algunos de los villanos más siniestros de Metrópolis en la parte 4 del episodio estreno.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: #SweetJustice Part 4
added.description: When six ordinary girls meet and discover that they each have extraordinary powers, they decide to join forces to take on one of Metropolis's most sinister villains.

added.title: Local Heroes/Pegatrix
added.description: Local Heroes: After the AO cause accidental destruction Dan's parents question whether the kids should be allowed to keep their Bakugan./Pegatrix: Lia disagrees with her new Bakugan Pegatrix on battle techniques but during a fierce fight Lia must rely on Pegatrix's battle savy.

added.title: Painbow
added.description: When a mysterious rainbow causes everyone to become unnaturally happy, the Powerpuff Girls must find where it ends to save the day and return Townsville to normal.

added.title: Frenemies/Strata's Fear
added.description: Frenemies: Two new Bakugan Brawlers, Shun and Magnus, try out for the AO./Strata's Fear: The AO solve the mystery of a kid's missing Bakugan and meet a Bakugan Hunter named Strata.

added.title: Dog Daze/In Focus
added.description: Dog Daze: Lightning discovers a new Bakugan, Artulean, leading to an unhealthy rivalry with Howlkor./In Focus: While Lia's newswoman mom does an expose on the AO Strata the Hunter tries to capture Hydorous.

added.title: Heroes locales
added.description: Los Fantásticos provocan una ola de destrucción por accidente, y los padres de Dan se preguntan si deberían permitirle a los niños conservar sus Bakugan.

added.title: Bye Bye, Bellum
added.description: The Mayor becomes dependent on the Powerpuff Girls after his assistant Ms. Bellum departs, leaving the girls so busy they accidentally hire the dangerous Bianca Bikini as his new assistant! When Bianca captures the Powerpuff Girls, the Mayor finds the tables turned and must rely on himself to help them.

added.title: Pegatrix
added.description: Lia no concuerda con las técnicas de Pegatrix, pero durante una intensa batalla, debe aprender a confiar en los conocimientos de su Bakugan.

added.title: Ene-amigos
added.description: Dos nuevos Peleadores Bakugan, Shun y Magnus, buscan ser parte de Los Fantásticos.

added.title: El miedo de Strata
added.description: Los Fantásticos resuelven la misteriosa desaparición del Bakugan de un niño, y conocen a un cazador de Bakugan llamado Strata.

added.title: Enredos perrunos
added.description: Lightning descubre un nuevo Bakugan, Artulean, y eso desata una fuerte rivalidad entre él y Howlkor.

added.title: Jamas Confies en un Humano
added.description: Mientras Aspheera busca vengarse del "Engañador Traicionero" que la traicionó, el ninja hace un sorprendente descubrimiento.

added.title: Bajo los reflectores
added.description: Cuando la reportera Verónica Venegas, madre de Lia, hace un reportaje acerca de Los Fantásticos, Strata El Cazador intenta capturar a Hydorous.

added.title: Sitiados
added.description: Habiendo aprendido que el Maestro Wu es el "Traicionero", los ninja se encuentran asediados en el Monasterio, tratando de proteger a Wu de la ira de Aspheera.

added.title: El Club de Exploradores
added.description: El ninja debe entrar en el Club del Explorador para obtener el segundo Pergamino de Spinjitzu Prohibido, en conflicto con el gerente del club y los miembros furiosos del club.

added.title: Man of the House
added.description: Clarence's first night home alone spirals out of control, forcing Clarence and his pals to wage war against their own home security measures.

added.title: Secrets
added.description: Grandpa Max's mysterious past comes to light when Vilgax shows up on earth in search of the Omnitrix. And the family must work together to defeat him.

added.title: Jefe por un dia
added.description: Cuando Chata deja que Vic sea el jefe del puesto de tacos por un día, él decide despedir a Val, lo que trae consecuencias desastrosas.

added.title: La Venganza es Mia
added.description: Aspheera llega al Monasterio de Spinjitzu y se enfrenta a Wu, obligando a uno de los ninjas a hacer un sacrificio heroico.

added.title: Una Fria Despedida
added.description: Habiendo aprendido que Zane no está muerto, el Maestro Wu se prepara para ir tras él, pero Lloyd y el otro ninja toman el asunto en sus propias manos y desafían a su Maestro.

added.title: Crece
added.description: Mientras todo el mundo celebra a Valentino porque le creció su primer vello facial, Vic se pone celoso y recurre a métodos mágicos para dejarse crecer el bigote y competir por la atención.

added.title: Nature Clarence
added.description: Clarence, Sumo and Jeff's nature hike veers off course courtesy of their under qualified, overwhelmed guide Josh, prompting Clarence to take the lead.

added.title: Bienvenidos al Inframundo Parte 1
added.description: Después de que Vic pierde una pelea de lucha libre, V&V viajan al inframundo para buscar el consejo de su tío, un famoso luchador llamado El Toro.

added.title: Lizard Day Afternoon
added.description: Clarence and Sumo chase a lizard to unexpected rewards as Jeff jockeys for playing time on Belson's spectacular new gaming system.

added.title: Sabelotodo
added.description: Cuando Vic accidentalmente libera malvados murciélagos de una cueva, depende de los chicos y de Don proteger el pueblo, pero la actitud de sabelotodo de Vic pone en peligro la tarea.

added.title: Duelo de globos
added.description: Cuando Vic es traicionado durante una guerra de globos de agua, emprende una vengativa misión para descubrir al responsable.

added.title: Nothing Ventured
added.description: Clarence and Sumo look to throw together some quick cash so they can invest in Chad and Sumo's dad's new business venture, a boutique sculpture shop.

added.title: T.G.I.S
added.description: The Secret Saturdays come to Bellwood to investigate a rash of chupacabra attacks.

added.title: O Mother, Where Art Thou?
added.description: Ma Vreedle threatens to blow up the sun if Ben and the Plumbers don't find her missing son!

added.title: Mud Is Thicker Than Water
added.description: Ben, Gwen and Cousin Lucy try to find out how Psyphon's thugs are getting Plumber technology.

added.title: The Ultimate Heist
added.description: Albedo seeks a device that will finally change him back into his Galvan form; meanwhile, Ben is locked in Plumber HQ prison.

added.title: For a Few Brains More
added.description: Ben, Rook and Max must stop Ultimate Albedo from absorbing Azmuth's intelligence and taking over the galaxy.

added.title: Lil Buddy
added.description: After playing a bit too aggressively with his Lil Buddy doll, Clarence gets timeout and his worst nightmare comes true. He misses the entire recess!

added.title: Hide and Secrets
added.description: Desperate for answers about Namagem, Mega Man decides to break into his father's lab, which leaves Suna exposed to the vengeful robot.

added.title: Make the Cut
added.description: Mega Man goes on a 24/7 heroing spree around the city, forcing Suna, Bert, Ashley, and Rush to deal with the problem at hand, Cut Man.

added.title: Panic in the Lighthouse
added.description: When Chaotique breaks into Dr. Light's lab, Mega Man must shut down his frenemy and the lab's defenses before either of them gets destroyed!

added.title: The Gauntlet Part 1
added.description: Lord Obsidian unites the Robot Masters against Mega Man and his family for an epic showdown at the Lighthouse.

added.title: The Gauntlet Part 2
added.description: As Dr. Light and Suna turn the Robot Masters against each other, Mega Man defeats and unmasks his arch nemeses, Lord Obsidian, who turns out to be Sgt. Night in disguise, and finally learns the identity of Namagem, Mega Man's long lost twin brother!

added.title: El Trampolin de Hamburguesa
added.description: Manzana y Cebollín deben encontrar una manera de usar el trampolín de Hamburguesa sin que él se sienta usado.

added.title: Lucha de Pulgares
added.description: El trío decide concursar en la competencia anual de Lucha de Pulgares, pero una sorpresa obliga a Mao Mao a lidiar con algo impensado… la derrota.

added.title: Ola de Calor
added.description: Manzana y Cebollín tratan de esparcir alegría durante una ola de calor en toda la ciudad.

added.title: Bobo Chan
added.description: Colosal adopta a un monstruo abandonado, pero es mejor dejar algunas cosas en estado salvaje.

added.title: El es el Sheriff
added.description: iEl trío lucha por deshacerse del Rey cuando los acompaña como nuevo ayudante del sheriff por un día!

added.title: Manzana Mandona
added.description: Manzana queda a cargo de la Tienda de Dolar por primera vez.

added.title: Conquista de Popularidad
added.description: Cuando Mao Mao descubre que no es tan popular como Colosal y Adorabat, sus amigos deciden reinventarlo en forma de un héroe más amable y tierno.

added.title: Todo Por Mao Mismo
added.description: El deseo de Mao Mao de convertirse en leyenda lo lleva a querer superarse a sí mismo una y otra vez. ¿Pero cuánto es suficiente?

added.title: Papel de Bano Bebecin
added.description: Manzana necesita conseguir la provisión del papel higiénico que usaría en toda su vida para terminar su escultura de arte moderno.

added.title: No es Gracioso
added.description: Cuando se acerca el aniversario de seis meses de amistad, Manzana tiene que encontrar una manera de no perder a su mejor amigo.

added.title: Origin of Species
added.description: Origin of Species, Part 1: Dan meets his partner Bakugan Drago for the first time and we learn about the incident that happened on Earth twelve years ago./Origin of Species, Part 2: Dan and friends win the Bakugan Battle, firmly establishing the Awesome Ones as our heroes and Bakugan Brawlers.

added.title: Burger Run/Monkey See, Monkey Don't
added.description: Burger Run: When the local Burger Joint is being threatened by a rogue Bakugan, Dan steps up to save the day and the burgers!/Monkey See, Monkey Don't: The AO stop neighborhood kids from copycat behavior (namely, using their Bakugan for frivolous reasons).

added.title: Bully for You/Trolling for Laughs
added.description: Bully for You: The AO must handle a neighborhood bully who is using his Bakugan to pick on the local kids./Trolling for Laughs: Wynton's constant practical jokes wear thin on his Bakugan Trox so the Bakugan decide to teach him a lesson.

added.title: Enemy of My Enemy
added.description: When a grudge match between Fire Man and Namagem threatens to level Silicon City, Mega Man must intervene and ultimately choose a side to prevent collateral damage.

added.title: Old School
added.description: Mega Man must stop Chaotique from making Silicon Central disappear, as in literally erasing the school at a subatomic level, while learning life lessons from a rambling old-bot named Hal.

added.title: This Is Not a Drill
added.description: Mega Man and Dr. Light must set aside a father-son disagreement to stop Drill Man from taking revenge on his own overbearing father.

added.title: A Man Man for All Seasons
added.description: When a run-in with the Hoover Gang leaves Aki unable to transform into Mega Man, he must don a cheap costume and enlist the unlikeliest of sidekicks, Man Man!

added.title: Change the Charge
added.description: Mega Man tries to stop Elec Man by helping him overcome his destructive habits, but is he being duped in the process?

added.title: #LaDulceJusticia - Primera parte
added.description: En el episodio estreno de cuatro partes de la serie, seis chicas comunes y corrientes se conocen y descubren que tienen poderes extraordinarios. Deciden unir sus fuerzas para derrotar a algunos de los villanos más siniestros de Metrópolis.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: #LaDulceJusticia - Segunda parte
added.description: Cuando seis chicas comunes y corrientes descubren que cada una tiene un poder extraordinario diferente, deciden unir fuerzas para derrotar a algunos de los villanos más siniestros de Metrópolis en la parte 2 del episodio estreno.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol
